description: Number of all self-avoiding planar walks of length j (0<=j<=n) starting at (0,0), ending at (n-j,0), remaining in the first quadrant and using steps (0,1), (1,0), (1,1), (-1,1), and (1,-1) with the restriction that (0,1) is never used below the diagonal and (1,0) is never used above the diagonal.
